11
00:00:59,893 --> 00:01:02,729
[Dae-su grunting]

12
00:01:03,646 --> 00:01:04,647
[Joon-yeong] Dae-su!

13
00:01:05,982 --> 00:01:06,900
Stop it.

14
00:01:08,902 --> 00:01:09,903
Dae-su! Get up!

15
00:01:13,907 --> 00:01:15,617
I said stop that!

16
00:01:17,327 --> 00:01:19,162
-[Cheong-san grunts]
-[growls]

17
00:01:21,539 --> 00:01:23,792
-Stop that!
-Hey!

18
00:01:23,875 --> 00:01:26,836
-[grunts]
-[Joon-yeong] Cheong-san! What the hell?

19
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:28,296
[thumping continues]

20
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:30,507
You son of a bitch!

21
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:32,342
[growling]

22
00:01:32,425 --> 00:01:33,718
[snarling]

23
00:01:33,802 --> 00:01:35,637
[grunting continues]

24
00:01:40,308 --> 00:01:41,434
Stop it!

25
00:01:47,065 --> 00:01:48,066
Let go!

26
00:01:48,942 --> 00:01:50,610
Get the fuck off me!

27
00:01:52,904 --> 00:01:53,905
Mom!

28
00:01:53,988 --> 00:01:56,199
[Cheong-san sobbing]

29
00:01:58,118 --> 00:02:00,036
Mom…
[cries]

30
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:02,372
[thunder rumbles]

31
00:02:02,455 --> 00:02:04,457
[growling]

32
00:02:07,585 --> 00:02:10,421
[thunder rumbles]

33
00:02:10,505 --> 00:02:12,006
[snarling]

34
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:23,184
[growling]

35
00:02:24,769 --> 00:02:25,895
Hurry.

36
00:02:27,355 --> 00:02:28,523
Run!

37
00:02:28,606 --> 00:02:30,150
[Wu-jin] Hey, let's go.

38
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:31,359
Hurry up!

39
00:02:31,442 --> 00:02:32,485
Let's go.

40
00:02:32,569 --> 00:02:33,695
[growls]

41
00:02:38,658 --> 00:02:39,993
Let's go, Cheong-san.

42
00:02:42,203 --> 00:02:43,788
Pull yourself together, man!

43
00:02:43,872 --> 00:02:46,040
[thunder rumbles]

44
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:48,168
Where are the others?

45
00:02:48,751 --> 00:02:49,586
What?

46
00:02:49,669 --> 00:02:51,129
[Joon-yeong] Where are they?

47
00:02:51,713 --> 00:02:53,464
-[Joon-yeong] What now?
-Did you see them coming?

48
00:02:53,548 --> 00:02:54,841
[snarls]

49
00:02:57,302 --> 00:02:58,469
Cheong-san, please.

50
00:02:58,553 --> 00:03:00,597
-Come with us.
-Let's go.

51
00:03:09,772 --> 00:03:12,942
-[thunder rumbling]
-[groaning]

52
00:03:19,741 --> 00:03:21,743
[somber music]

53
00:03:27,081 --> 00:03:29,334
[growling]

54
00:03:34,756 --> 00:03:36,090
Mom!

55
00:03:41,179 --> 00:03:43,014
Mom!

56
00:03:44,140 --> 00:03:46,142
[somber music continues]

57
00:04:06,037 --> 00:04:08,539
[growling]

58
00:04:17,215 --> 00:04:18,132
Mom…

59
00:04:18,716 --> 00:04:20,301
They're here. Hurry up!

60
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:21,719
[clanks]

61
00:04:21,803 --> 00:04:22,971
-Wu-jin!
-[Hyo-ryeong] Get up.

62
00:04:23,054 --> 00:04:25,515
Come on. We have to go. Let's go!

63
00:04:25,598 --> 00:04:26,933
[all panting]

64
00:04:30,395 --> 00:04:33,231
-[thunder rumbling]
-[growling]

65
00:04:36,192 --> 00:04:38,069
[lightning crackles]

66
00:04:38,152 --> 00:04:40,154
[all snarling]

67
00:04:48,538 --> 00:04:50,790
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

68
00:04:50,873 --> 00:04:52,458
Shut up. You're so heavy.

69
00:04:52,542 --> 00:04:55,169
[crying]
Mi-jin. Thank you so much.

70
00:04:56,963 --> 00:04:58,798
-Will you go out with me?
-No.

71
00:04:58,881 --> 00:05:00,049
Screw you.

72
00:05:00,675 --> 00:05:01,801
Hold on.

73
00:05:01,884 --> 00:05:03,511
[Joon-seong groans]

74
00:05:04,345 --> 00:05:06,347
-Why? What is it?
-Shh.

75
00:05:24,073 --> 00:05:24,949
Hear that?

76
00:05:26,326 --> 00:05:28,828
Those goddamn fucking zombies. Shit.

77
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:31,831
Let's go.

78
00:05:35,918 --> 00:05:36,836
Let's run.

79
00:05:36,919 --> 00:05:37,795
To the mountain.

80
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:43,676
Aah!

81
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:45,970
[zombies snarling]

82
00:05:50,850 --> 00:05:52,769
Ji-min. Help me.

83
00:05:52,852 --> 00:05:54,145
[breathes heavily]

84
00:05:54,228 --> 00:05:56,439
[zombie snarling]

85
00:06:04,238 --> 00:06:05,156
[Wu-jin] Hyo-ryeong!

86
00:06:06,532 --> 00:06:08,284
-[growls]
-[yelps]

87
00:06:11,245 --> 00:06:12,163
[Wu-jin] Get up!

88
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:16,584
[yelps]

89
00:06:19,253 --> 00:06:20,713
[zombie snarling]

90
00:06:22,215 --> 00:06:23,966
[thunder rumbles]

91
00:06:27,929 --> 00:06:28,846
Get up.

92
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:30,807
[whimpers]

93
00:06:35,853 --> 00:06:36,687
Sister.

94
00:06:37,563 --> 00:06:39,565
[hopeful music]

95
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,375
[whimpers]

96
00:06:58,251 --> 00:06:59,961
[growling]

97
00:07:00,878 --> 00:07:01,796
[yelps]

98
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:09,303
[whimpering]

99
00:07:16,269 --> 00:07:17,812
-Wu-jin.
-What are you doing here?

100
00:07:17,895 --> 00:07:18,855
Come on.

101
00:07:18,938 --> 00:07:19,939
Get going.

102
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:25,862
-Hey!
-Hyo-ryeong. You go first.

103
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:29,115
-Come on! Let's go!
-Let's go.

104
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:42,336
[all panting]

105
00:07:47,842 --> 00:07:48,843
What's wrong, Nam-ra?

106
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:52,305
Run.

107
00:07:54,765 --> 00:07:55,850
Let's go.

108
00:07:57,727 --> 00:07:59,604
[thunder rumbles]

109
00:07:59,687 --> 00:08:01,314
Oh, shit.

110
00:08:02,064 --> 00:08:03,024
[Su-hyeok] Run!

111
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:05,818
I'm gonna die tonight!

112
00:08:05,902 --> 00:08:07,987
-Run! Go!
-Just save yourselves!

113
00:08:08,488 --> 00:08:10,865
Just go! You'll die! Believe me!

114
00:08:10,948 --> 00:08:12,867
Whatever!
[grunts]

115
00:08:13,576 --> 00:08:15,620
-Over here!
-This way! Hurry!

116
00:08:15,703 --> 00:08:16,662
Come on!

117
00:08:25,671 --> 00:08:27,632
[Joon-seong] Are you crazy? Let go!

118
00:08:27,715 --> 00:08:30,218
[grunting]

119
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:34,597
Hey! No! No!

120
00:08:35,431 --> 00:08:36,557
[screams]
No!

121
00:08:36,641 --> 00:08:37,642
What are you doing?

122
00:08:37,725 --> 00:08:40,228
[Mi-jin] No! Let go of me, you assholes!

123
00:08:40,311 --> 00:08:41,729
Let me go!

124
00:08:41,812 --> 00:08:43,898
-[Joon-seong screams]
-Let go off me! No!

125
00:08:43,981 --> 00:08:45,900
Get out of here! Hurry!

126
00:08:47,026 --> 00:08:50,905
No! Joon-seong! Joon-seong…

127
00:08:50,988 --> 00:08:53,282
[Joon-seong screaming]

128
00:08:53,366 --> 00:08:55,034
Joon-seong!
[crying]

129
00:08:56,744 --> 00:08:58,538
[Mi-jin] No! Let me go!

130
00:08:58,621 --> 00:09:00,748
[growling]

131
00:09:00,831 --> 00:09:02,875
[screaming]

132
00:09:04,627 --> 00:09:05,878
Shit.

133
00:09:13,511 --> 00:09:14,679
Damn it.

134
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:21,769
[sobbing]

135
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:29,277
[breathes shakily]

136
00:09:31,112 --> 00:09:34,073
[Mi-jin sobbing]

137
00:09:40,162 --> 00:09:43,040
[mellow music]

138
00:10:12,153 --> 00:10:13,904
Hey, Cheong-san, I'm…

139
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:19,201
so sorry.

140
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:22,496
I didn't know she was your mom.

141
00:10:27,918 --> 00:10:28,794
I'm sorry.

142
00:10:33,174 --> 00:10:35,009
[clatters]

143
00:10:36,010 --> 00:10:38,012
[somber music]

144
00:10:59,241 --> 00:11:00,368
I'm sorry.

145
00:11:00,451 --> 00:11:02,411
[sobbing]

146
00:11:17,385 --> 00:11:18,344
Stop!

147
00:11:18,427 --> 00:11:19,970
-[crying]
-[snarls]

148
00:11:23,682 --> 00:11:24,892
Don't do this.

149
00:11:24,975 --> 00:11:27,978
[growling]

150
00:11:29,021 --> 00:11:31,023
No!
[screaming]

151
00:11:43,661 --> 00:11:46,997
[crying]

152
00:11:49,959 --> 00:11:51,710
Mommy…

153
00:11:51,794 --> 00:11:53,671
[crying]

154
00:12:02,596 --> 00:12:03,681
[growls]

155
00:12:12,982 --> 00:12:14,984
[thunder rumbles]

156
00:12:18,529 --> 00:12:20,531
[Byeong-chan] <i>A virus
must have a consistent pattern</i>

157
00:12:20,614 --> 00:12:22,158
<i>for us to create a vaccine.</i>

158
00:12:22,241 --> 00:12:23,742
[growling]

159
00:12:23,826 --> 00:12:25,327
<i>But the Jonas Virus…</i>

160
00:12:26,287 --> 00:12:28,539
<i>transforms and evolves on its own.</i>

161
00:12:28,622 --> 00:12:30,374
[growling]

162
00:12:30,458 --> 00:12:32,543
<i>It is an ever-changing monster.</i>

163
00:12:34,211 --> 00:12:35,796
[growls]

164
00:12:36,755 --> 00:12:38,674
<i>It's impossible to create a vaccine.</i>

165
00:12:39,550 --> 00:12:41,177
<i>There is only one solution.</i>

166
00:12:44,972 --> 00:12:46,056
<i>Slaughter.</i>

167
00:12:47,683 --> 00:12:50,311
<i>Completely burning and killing the host,</i>

168
00:12:50,394 --> 00:12:52,730
<i>so not a single cell remains.</i>

169
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:58,027
<i>The moment we are consumed by arrogance
and think we can defeat the virus,</i>

170
00:12:59,403 --> 00:13:01,030
<i>humankind will end.</i>

171
00:13:05,242 --> 00:13:07,495
The file was massive,
so we couldn't analyze it all,

172
00:13:07,578 --> 00:13:09,997
but a significant portion
of it is credible, sir.

173
00:13:10,789 --> 00:13:12,416
And where is the proof for that?

174
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:17,379
Well, KDCA is creating a virus
using the exact method he described.

175
00:13:18,964 --> 00:13:20,508
If they create the same virus,

176
00:13:20,591 --> 00:13:23,344
then the KDCA will conclude it's credible.

177
00:13:23,427 --> 00:13:25,513
[scoffs]
Well…

178
00:13:27,348 --> 00:13:30,017
Many soldiers are going insane
from this thing, but…

179
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:32,770
It's scarier when a scientist goes crazy.

180
00:13:32,853 --> 00:13:34,772
Did you hear
they're expanding martial law?

181
00:13:36,065 --> 00:13:36,982
Martial law?

182
00:13:37,816 --> 00:13:39,944
Why would they do that
if we're handling it well?

183
00:13:40,528 --> 00:13:42,488
My friend in the NIS analysis team

184
00:13:42,571 --> 00:13:45,658
said they're discussing pulling back
the blockade to Yangdong

185
00:13:45,741 --> 00:13:47,201
and expanding martial law.

186
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:52,706
What about Hyosan?

187
00:13:55,459 --> 00:13:57,586
I think they're willing
to make sacrifices.

188
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:03,008
[sighs]

189
00:14:06,262 --> 00:14:08,722
We may have ceased
our rescue operation for now, but…

190
00:14:10,182 --> 00:14:13,060
there might not be another time
to rescue survivors.

191
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:17,773
Strengthen the blockade
on the outskirts of Hyosan.

192
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:22,236
The moment the blockade
is penetrated by the infected,

193
00:14:24,071 --> 00:14:25,614
we'll have to step up and…

194
00:14:26,991 --> 00:14:28,492
abandon Hyosan.

195
00:14:29,243 --> 00:14:31,245
[suspenseful music]

196
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:33,706
[party leader] Take this.

197
00:14:40,004 --> 00:14:41,338
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

198
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:48,220
Childish to think the party leader
came personally to save me.

199
00:14:49,096 --> 00:14:50,389
You came to dump me.

200
00:14:50,472 --> 00:14:52,516
My NIS source says

201
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:56,186
something is going to happen very soon
in Hyosan.

202
00:14:56,979 --> 00:15:00,774
In your district.
If something bad really does happen,

203
00:15:00,858 --> 00:15:04,695
I'll say you even resigned from your post
thinking it would help prevent it.

204
00:15:04,778 --> 00:15:07,114
No one would even think of blaming you.

205
00:15:07,197 --> 00:15:08,532
Blame me for what?

206
00:15:08,616 --> 00:15:11,869
Trust me, you're gonna sign it.

207
00:15:11,952 --> 00:15:15,414
I'll protect your political career
until the end.

208
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:19,543
Do you need time to think it over?

209
00:15:19,627 --> 00:15:21,420
You failed Hyosan.

210
00:15:25,466 --> 00:15:26,634
They'll just abandon it?

211
00:15:27,509 --> 00:15:29,178
Sign it within the day,

212
00:15:29,261 --> 00:15:33,182
and hand it to the person in charge
of this place.

213
00:15:33,265 --> 00:15:34,183
[sighs]

214
00:15:37,811 --> 00:15:39,063
[sighs]

215
00:15:43,359 --> 00:15:44,777
Hmm…

216
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:51,116
Sir, um, can you hear me?

217
00:15:52,034 --> 00:15:53,786
-[party leader] Let's go.
-Excuse me, sir!

218
00:15:53,869 --> 00:15:55,120
Oh, damn.

219
00:15:55,204 --> 00:15:57,998
Assemblywoman?
You're getting us out now, right?

220
00:15:58,082 --> 00:16:01,585
The party leader came,
so it'll all be resolved very soon, right?

221
00:16:02,127 --> 00:16:05,422
[Dal-ho] He says he'll save us, right?

222
00:16:06,048 --> 00:16:06,966
Ma'am?

223
00:16:27,528 --> 00:16:30,406
[glass shatters]

224
00:16:53,762 --> 00:16:55,764
[birds chirping]

225
00:17:46,315 --> 00:17:47,232
[sighs]

226
00:17:51,111 --> 00:17:52,738
I thought about it all night long.

227
00:17:54,656 --> 00:17:55,824
How do I live?

228
00:17:58,118 --> 00:17:59,244
What do I do?

229
00:18:10,130 --> 00:18:12,007
Why don't we talk about this later?

230
00:18:13,675 --> 00:18:15,636
Tomorrow or the day after.

231
00:18:15,719 --> 00:18:17,012
Or next week, maybe.

232
00:18:17,096 --> 00:18:19,306
[soft music]

233
00:18:19,389 --> 00:18:21,391
Let's get out of here and eat some food,

234
00:18:21,934 --> 00:18:24,144
and shower first, okay?

235
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:25,395
We'll talk about it then.

236
00:18:26,271 --> 00:18:27,147
Hmm?

237
00:18:33,445 --> 00:18:35,322
We have a lot to talk about, you know?

238
00:18:37,574 --> 00:18:39,243
Let's give it time.

239
00:18:47,835 --> 00:18:49,837
[soft music continues]

240
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:54,466
Whatever happens…

241
00:18:56,385 --> 00:18:57,511
please don't give up.

242
00:19:00,055 --> 00:19:01,014
Okay?

243
00:19:05,727 --> 00:19:06,603
Okay.

244
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:17,656
Never.

245
00:19:20,784 --> 00:19:21,660
Mm-hmm.

246
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:23,954
You too.

247
00:19:26,373 --> 00:19:27,207
Mm-hmm.

248
00:19:28,792 --> 00:19:29,793
It'll be okay.

249
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:34,006
[suspenseful music]

250
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:56,111
[panting]

251
00:20:00,449 --> 00:20:01,783
[yelps]

252
00:20:03,660 --> 00:20:05,037
[groaning]

253
00:20:13,754 --> 00:20:15,422
[groans]

254
00:20:17,758 --> 00:20:19,092
[groans]

255
00:20:32,648 --> 00:20:33,523
[Su-hyeok] What is it?

256
00:20:34,650 --> 00:20:35,776
Do you see something?

257
00:20:41,406 --> 00:20:43,325
The smell is stronger.

258
00:20:46,411 --> 00:20:48,413
[sniffs]

259
00:20:49,915 --> 00:20:52,000
[sniffing continues]

260
00:20:54,169 --> 00:20:55,837
I can't really smell anything.

261
00:20:57,172 --> 00:20:59,258
I think they're all coming this way.

262
00:20:59,841 --> 00:21:01,093
The smell is really strong.

263
00:21:02,970 --> 00:21:06,306
Doesn't matter.
We're all trapped in here for good now.

264
00:21:07,307 --> 00:21:08,642
And there's no way to get out.

265
00:21:10,394 --> 00:21:11,728
Please don't say that.

266
00:21:12,980 --> 00:21:13,814
So don't.

267
00:21:14,690 --> 00:21:15,816
I think we're done.

268
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:18,068
Ah, damn it!

269
00:21:18,694 --> 00:21:20,279
Let them kill us if they want.

270
00:21:25,367 --> 00:21:26,326
[sighs]

271
00:21:29,538 --> 00:21:31,164
-[Wu-jin] Ha-ri.
-[exhales deeply]

272
00:21:32,082 --> 00:21:35,085
[Wu-jin] You didn't fail
in the preliminaries, did you?

273
00:21:37,546 --> 00:21:38,380
No.

274
00:21:39,589 --> 00:21:40,674
I did really well.

